frameDefinitions: An Entity ends up with a particular new Final_quality.
An Agent removes a Theme from a Source so that the it is in the Agent's possession.
The Invader enters a Land in an aggressive attempt to cripple or dominate its people and its government.
These are words describing situations in which a Perpetrator takes Goods from a  Victim or a Source.
This frame describes a Theme losing its autonomy and perhaps sustaining material damage as the result of a successful invasion on the behalf of a Conqueror.
A Recipient starts off without the Theme in their possession, and then comes to possess it.
frameExamples: Milton <t>took</t> the can of beer out of the refrigerator.
In August 1990 ,Iraq was <t>invading</t> Kuwait , which led to the Gulf war .
I can't believe he <t>pickpocketed</t> my gold watch !
The Spaniards <t>conquered</t> the Incas with both the Cross and the arquebus
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change so that it possesses the <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
The quality that the <fen>Entity</fen> has at the end of the event.
When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
The person who takes possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> takes possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location of the <fen>Theme</fen> prior to the taking.
When the taking takes place.
Where the taking takes place.
The political area that is being crippled by the <fen>Invader</fen>'s entry.
The army or other self-directed entity that is entering the <fen>Land</fen> in a hostile manner.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Invader</fen> invades <fen>Land</fen>.
This role identifies the location where the <fen>Invader</fen> invades the <fen>Land</fen>.
<fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) that takes the goods away.
<fen>Victim</fen> is the person (or other sentient being or group) that owns the goods before they are taken away by the perpetrator.
<fen>Goods</fen> is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be taken away.
<fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the goods, before they change location.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the theft occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the theft occurs.
The <fen>Conqueror</fen> is the entity that overtakes the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the land, government, and its people that is seized by the <fen>Conqueror</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Conqueror</fen> seizes the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Conqueror</fen> takes over the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Recipient</fen> indicates the entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes possession.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> denotes where the Getting takes place.
